rules:
- id: rule-promotion-requires-evidence
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Pattern promotion to core must be supported by strong evidence from multiple
    sources to prevent weak or context-specific patterns from becoming foundational.
  title: Rule Promotion Requires Evidence
- id: rule-shared-knowledge-workspace
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Projects must use the shared Knowledge Workspace and avoid duplicating
    governance structures to ensure reusable intelligence and idempotent onboarding.
  title: Rule Shared Knowledge Workspace
- id: rule-decisions-must-be-persisted
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: All architectural decisions must be persisted as structured ADRs before
    being reflected in other artefacts to ensure traceability and a single source
    of truth.
  title: Rule Decisions Must Be Persisted
- compliance:
    enabled: true
  id: rule-decision-schema-must-be-structured
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: All decisions must be expressed using a structured YAML decision schema
    rather than unstructured narrative text to enable machine processing.
  title: Rule Decision Schema Must Be Structured
- compliance:
    enabled: true
  id: rule-pattern-decision-lifecycle-alignment
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Ensure consistent interpretation between pattern maturity and decision
    lifecycle status to prevent premature promotion and inconsistent system state.
  title: Rule Pattern Decision Lifecycle Alignment
- id: rule-do-not-merge-across-architectural-layers
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Patterns must not be merged across different architectural layers to preserve
    separation between governance, execution, contracts, and reliability.
  title: Rule Do Not Merge Across Architectural Layers
- id: rule-decision-status-drives-stage
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: The lifecycle stage of architecture items must be derived from their decision
    status, preventing items not marked 'accepted' from appearing as 'DONE'.
  title: Rule Decision Status Drives Stage
- id: rule-language-semantic-contract
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Defines the semantic contract for architecture artefacts, distinguishing
    between intent and state, and establishing standard lifecycle terminology.
  title: Rule Language Semantic Contract
- id: rule-signal-promotion-criteria
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Candidate signals promote to patterns only when satisfying recurrence,
    impact, reusability, and stability criteria supported by observable evidence.
  title: Rule Signal Promotion Criteria
- id: rule-patterns-born-as-supporting
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: All patterns must be created as supporting by default to ensure they are
    validated through evidence before becoming foundational commitments.
  title: Rule Patterns Born As Supporting
- id: rule-aem-consistency-with-decisions
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: The Architecture Evolution Map (AEM) must reflect and never contradict
    Architecture Decision Records (ADR) to maintain governance integrity.
  title: Rule Aem Consistency With Decisions
- id: rule-workflow-execution-model-compliance
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Runtime-native workflows must conform to the CAS Workflow Execution Model,
    ensuring separation of concerns between orchestration, reasoning, and knowledge
    access.
  title: Rule Workflow Execution Model Compliance
- compliance:
    enabled: true
  id: rule-adr-single-source-of-truth
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Architecture decisions must be recorded and updated only in ADRs, with
    all other representations derived from them to prevent inconsistencies.
  title: Rule Adr Single Source Of Truth
- id: rule-precedence-hierarchy
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Defines the precedence model (Global > Project > Prompt) for resolving
    conflicts, ensuring global rules act as immutable system-wide invariants.
  title: Rule Precedence Hierarchy
- id: rule-system-proposes-architect-decides
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Maintains human-in-the-loop control by requiring that all system-proposed
    architectural decisions be explicitly accepted, rejected, or deferred by an architect.
  title: Rule System Proposes Architect Decides
- id: rule-core-patterns-must-be-foundational
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Core patterns must represent foundational architectural primitives rather
    than specific strategies to ensure long-term architectural stability.
  title: Rule Core Patterns Must Be Foundational
- id: rule-heuristic-patterns-require-signals
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: All heuristic-derived patterns must include at least one linked signal
    as evidence to ensure grounding in observed behaviour.
  title: Rule Heuristic Patterns Require Signals
summary:
  global_rules: 17
  project_rules: 0
  total_rules: 17
